36. Create an array of fruits in PHP and display the third element.
ANSWER
<?php
// Create an array of fruits
$fruits = array("Apple", "Banana", "Cherry", "Mango", "Orange");

// Check if the third element exists before displaying it
if (isset($fruits[2])) {
    echo "The third fruit is: " . $fruits[2];
} else {
    echo "The third fruit does not exist in the array.";
}
?>

OUTPUT
The third fruit is: Cherry
